### Define RxDB Schema with Default Values (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/rx-schema.md

This code illustrates how to define a collection schema in RxDB with default values for fields. The 'default' attribute is used for fields like 'age', ensuring that unset fields are populated with this value upon document insertion. Defaults are only applicable to first-level fields.

```javascript
const schemaWithDefaultAge = {
  version: 0,
  primaryKey: 'id',
  type: 'object',
  properties: {
      id: {
          type: 'string',
          maxLength: 100 // <- the primary key must have set maxLength
      },
      firstName: {
          type: 'string'
      },
      lastName: {
          type: 'string'
      },
      age: {
          type: 'integer',
          default: 20       // <- default will be used
      }
  },
  required: ['id']
};

```

