### Define RxDB Schema with Final Fields (JavaScript)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/rx-schema.md

This snippet shows how to define a schema in RxDB where certain fields are marked as 'final'. Final fields cannot be modified after insertion and are always considered required. This can improve data integrity and performance with specific RxDB features like 'eventReduce'.

```javascript
const schemaWithFinalAge = {
  version: 0,
  primaryKey: 'id',
  type: 'object',
  properties: {
      id: {
          type: 'string',
          maxLength: 100 // <- the primary key must have set maxLength
      },
      firstName: {
          type: 'string'
      },
      lastName: {
          type: 'string'
      },
      age: {
          type: 'integer',
          final: true
      }
  },
  required: ['id']
};

```

