### Define Composite Primary Key Schema (JSON)

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs-src/docs/rx-schema.md

This JSON defines an RxDB schema with a composite primary key. The 'id' field is designated as the primary key, composed of 'firstName', 'lastName', and a '|' separator. Key compression is also enabled.

```json
{
  "keyCompression": true,
  "version": 0,
  "title": 'human schema with composite primary',
  "primaryKey": {
      "key": 'id',
      "fields": [
          'firstName',
          'lastName'
      ],
      "separator": '|'
  },
  "type": 'object',
  "properties": {
      "id": {
          "type": 'string',
          "maxLength": 100
      },
      "firstName": {
          "type": 'string'
      },
      "lastName": {
          "type": 'string'
      }
  },
  "required": [
    'id', 
    'firstName',
    'lastName'
  ]
}
```

