### RxDB Schema for Indexed Embeddings

Source: https://github.com/pubkey/rxdb/blob/master/docs/articles/javascript-vector-database.html

Defines an RxDB collection schema designed to store embeddings and their corresponding index values. Index fields are standardized to strings of length 10 for sortability and precision, suitable for similarity search.

```javascript
const indexSchema = {    type: 'string',    maxLength: 10};
const schema = {
    "version": 0,
    "primaryKey": "id",
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
        "id": {
            "type": "string",
            "maxLength": 100
        },
        "embedding": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
                "type": "number"
            }
        },
        // index fields
        "idx0": indexSchema,
        "idx1": indexSchema,
        "idx2": indexSchema,
        "idx3": indexSchema,
        "idx4": indexSchema
    },
    "required": [
        "id",
        "embedding",
        "idx0",
        "idx1",
        "idx2",
        "idx3",
        "idx4"
    ],
    "indexes": [
        "idx0",
        "idx1",
        "idx2",
        "idx3",
        "idx4"
    ]
}
```

